text:
="preserve">Marian Cycoń (17 July 1940 – 20 November 2020) was a Polish politician. He was born in Barcice Dolne, Poland. He was a member of Sejm from 1997 to 2001 and again from 2011 to 2015. He also was the Mayor of Nowy Sącz from 1988 to 1990 and of Stary Sącz from 1995 to 1998 and again from 2002 to 2011.
Cycoń died on 20 November 2020 at the age of 80.
